[SN]TITLE[SN]
Bridgend Urdd Eisteddfod festival begins in Pencoed

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
The 2017 Urdd Eisteddfod begins on Monday in Bridgend county.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The Welsh-language arts festival will run from 29 May to 3 June at Bridgend College's Pencoed Campus.
When it approved the event, the council said it hoped it would bring 100,000 visitors and Â£6m to the local economy.
The festival, which has been running for nearly 90 years, includes activities, performances and competitions.
